# RAI – Your AI Companion

A futuristic cyberpunk AI chat companion powered by Claude. Supports text and voice interaction with a 2D animated avatar.

---

## 🚀 Quick Start

### 1. Clone and install

```bash
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/rai-ai-companion.git
cd rai-ai-companion
npm install
```

### 2. Add your Anthropic API key

The app calls the Anthropic API directly from the browser. You have two options:

**Option A — Vite environment variable (recommended):**

Create a `.env` file in the project root:

```
VITE_ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
```

Then update the fetch call in `src/App.jsx`:

```js
headers: {
  "Content-Type": "application/json",
  "x-api-key": import.meta.env.VITE_ANTHROPIC_API_KEY,
  "anthropic-version": "2023-06-01",
  "anthropic-dangerous-direct-browser-access": "true",
},
```

**Option B — Proxy backend (production-safe):**

Set up a lightweight Express / Next.js / Vercel Edge Function that forwards requests to the Anthropic API with your key stored server-side.

> ⚠️ Never commit your API key to a public repository.

### 3. Run locally

```bash
npm run dev
```

Open [http://localhost:3000](http://localhost:3000)

---

## 📁 File Structure

```
rai-ai-companion/
├── index.html          # HTML entry point
├── package.json        # Dependencies & scripts
├── vite.config.js      # Vite configuration
└── src/
    ├── main.jsx        # React root mount
    ├── App.jsx         # Main application component
    └── styles.css      # All styles & animations
```

---

## ☁️ Deploy to Vercel (free)

```bash
npm install -g vercel
vercel
```

Add `VITE_ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` as an environment variable in the Vercel dashboard.

## ☁️ Deploy to Netlify (free)

```bash
npm run build
# Drag and drop the /dist folder to netlify.com/drop
```

Or connect your GitHub repo directly in Netlify and set:
- **Build command:** `npm run build`
- **Publish directory:** `dist`
- Add `VITE_ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` in Site Settings → Environment Variables

## ☁️ Deploy to GitHub Pages

```bash
npm install --save-dev gh-pages
```

Add to `package.json` scripts:
```json
"predeploy": "npm run build",
"deploy": "gh-pages -d dist"
```

Then:
```bash
npm run deploy
```

---

## ✨ Features

- 💬 Real-time chat with Claude (Sonnet)
- 🎙 Voice input via Web Speech API
- 🔊 Text-to-speech responses
- 🤖 2D animated cyberpunk avatar
- ⚙️ Settings panel (voice, gender, history)
- 📱 Fully mobile responsive
- 🌌 Cyberpunk dark theme with neon blue glows

---

## 🛠 Tech Stack

- **React 18** + **Vite**
- **Anthropic Claude API** (claude-sonnet-4)
- **Web Speech API** (SpeechRecognition + SpeechSynthesis)
- Pure CSS animations — no animation library needed

